Questions:
What is the primary goal of the CARE research study?
A) To compare the effectiveness of apixaban and enoxaparin in preventing blood clots after bladder removal surgery;
B) To test a new experimental blood thinner for post-surgery patients;
C) To evaluate the long-term side effects of blood thinners in patients who have not undergone surgery;
D) To determine the best surgical techniques for bladder removal.

Correct answer: A) To compare the effectiveness of apixaban and enoxaparin in preventing blood clots after bladder removal surgery.

If you decide not to participate in the CARE study, what standard care option will you be offered following your bladder removal surgery?
A) You will not receive any blood thinners after surgery;
B) You will be given a prescription for a blood thinner and instructed to self-administer it until 30 days after surgery;
C) You will be required to stay in the hospital for 30 days for monitoring;
D) You will be given a placebo instead of a blood thinner.

Correct answer: B
